<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,281,811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,282,308]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,288,305]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,282,308]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">.</emphasis>
Historically there has been confusion in differentiating the taxa 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1892" box="[994,1080,281,307]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tympanoterpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergi">
<emphasis box="[994,1080,281,307]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. bergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1905 d" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[1136,1388,281,308]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Proarna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bufo">
<emphasis box="[1136,1215,281,307]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. bufo</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[1222,1388,281,308]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="304 - 319" refId="ref104422" refString="Distant, W. L. (1905 d) Rhynchotal notes XXX. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 15, 304 - 319. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745480509443047" type="journal article" year="1905">Distant, 1905d</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
due to the slight differences in the morphology of the two species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S." box="[853,1132,317,343]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref108909" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Sanborn &amp; Heath (2014)</bibRefCitation>
determined a geographical separation between the species with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[562,640,353,379]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Proarna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bufo">
<emphasis box="[562,640,353,379]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. bufo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in central and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1022,1133,353,379]" name="Argentina" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Argentina</collectingCountry>
while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1892" box="[1210,1297,353,379]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tympanoterpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergi">
<emphasis box="[1210,1297,353,379]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. bergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was distributed in the northern and western parts of the country. This along with differences in morphology noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobi, A." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref105512" refString="Jacobi, A. (1907) Homoptera Andina. Die Zikaden des kordillerengebietes von Sudamerika nach systematik und Verbreitung. I. Cicadidae. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Enthnographischen Museums zu Dresden, 11, 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930709487386" type="journal article" year="1907">Jacobi (1907)</bibRefCitation>
was used to clarify the Bolivian specimens cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[808,984,425,452]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="304 - 319" refId="ref104422" refString="Distant, W. L. (1905 d) Rhynchotal notes XXX. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 15, 304 - 319. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745480509443047" type="journal article" year="1905">Distant (1905d)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobi, A." box="[1037,1189,425,451]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref105512" refString="Jacobi, A. (1907) Homoptera Andina. Die Zikaden des kordillerengebietes von Sudamerika nach systematik und Verbreitung. I. Cicadidae. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Enthnographischen Museums zu Dresden, 11, 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930709487386" type="journal article" year="1907">Jacobi (1907)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1892" box="[1225,1310,425,451]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tympanoterpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergi">
<emphasis box="[1225,1310,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. bergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sanborn 2019 b)" baseAuthorityName="Sanborn" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[151,428,461,488]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Proarna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bufo">
<emphasis box="[151,229,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. bufo</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[243,420,461,488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,281,811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This is the only Peruvian species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[607,701,498,523]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Proarna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,701,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Proarna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is unicolorous dark brown with an abdomen that slightly expands laterally from the base to segment 5 before curving to the terminus. No other Peruvian species exhibits this coloration or abdominal shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,281,811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,219,606,632]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[219,350,612,629]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">DISTRIBUTION</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[350,357,606,632]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">.</emphasis>
The species has been reported previously from 
<collectingCountry box="[913,1024,605,631]" name="Argentina" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[1041,1212,605,631]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref106666" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref104819" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A. (1985) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica 34. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrect, 414 pp." type="book" year="1985">Duffels &amp; van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
; Sanborn 2013; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S." box="[451,709,641,667]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref108909" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Sanborn &amp; Heath 2014</bibRefCitation>
) with recent records expanding the distribution to include 
<collectingCountry box="[1354,1436,641,667]" name="Bolivia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[159,337,677,704]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
). Previous references to 
<collectingCountry box="[614,724,677,703]" name="Colombia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Colombia</collectingCountry>
were shown to be erroneous (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S." box="[1065,1333,677,703]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref108909" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Sanborn &amp; Heath 2014</bibRefCitation>
). It is associated with grasses in various habitats and is endothermic (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, J. E. &amp; Heath, M. S. &amp; Noriega, F. G." box="[835,1072,713,740]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="319 - 328" refId="ref108772" refString="Sanborn, A. F., Heath, J. E., Heath, M. S., and Noriega, F. G. (1995 a) Thermoregulation by endogenous heat production in two South American grass dwelling cicadas (Homoptera: Cicadidae: Proarna). Florida Entomologist, 78, 319 - 328. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3495905" type="journal article" year="1995">
Sanborn 
<emphasis box="[937,986,713,739]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 1995a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
